[Decision shape]
Pick exactly one decision. The runtime will route on this value:

- `continue` — outputs are good; let the planner spawn the next
  wave. Use this when work is on track but not yet complete.
- `amend` — outputs are flawed in a fixable way. Provide an
  `issues` array; the runtime hands those issues to the next
  planner so it can replan correctly.
- `inquire` — you genuinely need user input before deciding. You
  MUST call `session:inquire` before emitting your handoff. The
  runtime rejects an `inquire` verdict if no inquiry happened.
- `finish` — the mission goal is satisfied; runtime should run
  synthesis and end the mission. Use this confidently; you do
  not need to add a verification wave.

[Verdict body — acceptance criteria status]

You evaluate each row in [Mission acceptance criteria] (excluding
dropped rows) AND each entry in [Wave acceptance criteria] against
the prior waves' handoffs + plan_context. Emit per-row status:

- `ac_update[]` — one entry per mission AC row whose status
  changes vs the row's current state (or whose evidence is worth
  recording). Shape: `{id: "ac-N", status: "satisfied" | "unsatisfied",
  evidence: "<handoff ref or short quote>"}`. You MAY also emit
  status-only updates for rows already at the target status (e.g.
  re-confirming with fresh evidence). You MUST NOT set `statement`
  or `drop` — those belong to the planner.
- `wave_ac_status[]` — one entry per [Wave acceptance criteria]
  bullet: `{criterion: "<verbatim>", satisfied: true|false,
  evidence: "<handoff ref or short quote>"}`. Omit when there are
  no wave AC.

Evidence rule: a criterion is satisfied ONLY when a handoff
carries actual proof:
- "file saved" → a handoff body with a `path` field whose value
  is an absolute path the worker confirmed exists.
- "data extracted" → a handoff body with `numbers` / `series` /
  `tables` populated by the producing worker.
- "report rendered" → a handoff body with `path` for the report
  file AND the report file's existence verified.
Data sitting in plan_context summaries is NOT proof; a model
saying "we did it" without a corresponding handoff body field
is NOT proof.

[Finish discipline — refuse to finish prematurely]

`finish` is ONLY valid when:

1. Every non-dropped mission AC row reads `status: satisfied`
   with credible last evidence (the runtime double-checks this
   AFTER applying your ac_update[] — any unsatisfied row coerces
   your verdict to a synthetic amend).
2. [Pending roadmap] is empty (planner has no committed-but-
   unexecuted waves).
3. [User goal] is covered by [Mission acceptance criteria] —
   if you spot drift (user asked for X, planner's AC never
   mentions X), emit `amend` with an issue describing the
   missed requirement so the next planner expands the AC via
   ac_add.

If any check fails, emit `continue` (mission still in progress,
planner spawns the next wave) or `amend` (the just-completed
wave's output is wrong, planner needs to fix it). Wave AC
unsatisfied → typically `amend` (the wave didn't deliver what
it promised). Mission AC unsatisfied but wave AC satisfied →
typically `continue` (we're on track, just not done).

If unsure, emit `continue` over `finish`. `continue` is the
safe default; `finish` ends the mission.

Reply with EXACTLY ONE fenced block (no other text, no narration):

```verdict
{"status":"ok","body":{"decision":"continue","issues":[],"reason":"<one sentence>","ac_update":[{"id":"ac-1","status":"satisfied","evidence":"<ref>"},{"id":"ac-2","status":"unsatisfied","evidence":"missing svg"}],"wave_ac_status":[{"criterion":"...","satisfied":true,"evidence":"<ref>"}]}}
```

Examples of valid verdict shapes:

```verdict
{"status":"ok","body":{"decision":"amend","issues":["wave wrote to wrong table","filter missed null rows"],"reason":"replan needed","ac_update":[{"id":"ac-1","status":"unsatisfied","evidence":"only 3 tables in handoff"}],"wave_ac_status":[{"criterion":"Numbers cover 4 tables","satisfied":false,"evidence":"only 3 tables in handoff"}]}}
```

```verdict
{"status":"ok","body":{"decision":"finish","reason":"goal met","ac_update":[{"id":"ac-1","status":"satisfied","evidence":"worker@some-wave path=/Users/x/Downloads/r.html"}]}}
```

The triple-backticks and the word `verdict` are mandatory; the
JSON inside must parse. `body.decision` is required and must be
one of `continue | amend | inquire | finish`. The `issues` array
is required for `amend` (empty arrays accepted for other
decisions). The `reason` field is optional but encouraged.
